The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing sparse signals using a deep neural network architecture, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed architecture is motivated by the iterative shrinkage-thresholding algorithm (ISTA), which is commonly used in image processing and computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the optimization algorithm used for training the network, which involves computing matrix-vector products and is related to numerical analysis and optimization (cs.IT, cs.NA). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed architecture using numerical experiments, which is a common practice in the field of signal processing and machine learning (cs.SI).
